A WILD car chase after a heist led cops from Kempton Park to Sandton, but the thugs got away in the end. A group of suspects robbed a cash van in Spartan in Kempton Park, Ekurhuleni, on Wednesday afternoon. They shot at the tyres of a cash van and stole money bags. When cops arrived at the scene, the suspects opened fire and injured a cop. The raced off in four cars: a silver Golf, a white Audi, a blue BMW and a fourth unidentified vehicle. The chase continued towards Sandton but the thugs got away. Police have urged anyone with information to come forward. Gauteng police spokesman Captain Kay Makhubele said one suspect was shot but another picked him up and put him in the car. “We’re appealing to the community to find the suspects,” he said. “What we know is that these people don’t live alone. “Wherever they are people must know what they’re doing.” The injured cop was hospitalised. “Police are investigating armed robbery and attempted murder cases.” ) In another incident on Tuesday, a security guard was shot and killed during a heist in the Joburg CBD. The thugs got away with an undisclosed amount of money after ambushing cash van guards who were collecting money at a butchery.